{"by":"kunley","id":47700973,"kids":[47702824],"parent":47700460,"text":"Working on an audio streaming platform powering an indy internet radio. Looks like Icecast &amp; friends show its age and a similar product can be easily built with the functionality cast down to simply robust streaming &amp; handling &quot;timed playlists&quot;. I enjoy every bit of knowing exactly what happens in the code. It&#x27;s not open source atm, but will be. It&#x27;s in Go, is a pleasure to write and the deployment takes minimal amount of resources.<p>Other project is to continue a bit stalled progress of a configuration language BCL - add functions, more structures and fix some hidden scoping issues. Making languages is an endless fun.\n<a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;wkhere&#x2F;bcl\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;wkhere&#x2F;bcl</a>","time":1775724920,"type":"comment"}